enterAsLong(address).details: Counterparty joins and activates the contract.

exercise(uint256,address).details: Exercises the contract after resolution, calculating payout based on the polynomial.      x = (S - K) / K            (all 1e18 fixed-point; signed, dimensionless)      y = x^5 - 5x^3 + 4x      scaled = clamp(y / L, -1, +1)      ratio  = (1 + scaled) / 2

fund(uint256,uint256).details: Funds the contract and sets strike price (same logic as previous Genie).

params.strikeNotional: Amount of strike token provided if maker is long.

getOracleAddress().details: Returns the oracle address used by this contract.

initialize(address,address,address,strin.details: Initializes the PolynomialGenie contract clone. Called via the GenieBook.

reclaim(address).details: Allows the short side to reclaim funds if the contract expires without exercise.

resolve().details: Resolves the price at expiry from the oracle (callable by anyone after expiry).

setFullPayLine(uint256).details: Sets the vertical 100%-line L (>0). When |y|>=L, one side gets 100%.
